<item>
            <title>[POOL-158] References to GenericKeyedObjectPool._minIdle are not always synchronized</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/POOL-158</link>
                <project id="12310488" key="POOL">Commons Pool</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;References to GenericKeyedObjectPool._minIdle are not always synchronized:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The ensureMinIdle() and evict() methods both access the field outside the synch. block.&lt;br/&gt;
This is particularly bad as they are called from the timer thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The references could use getMinIdle(), which is synch., or it would probably be cheaper to move the references into the synch. blocks.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Better yet, can the field be made final? setMinIdle() is currently only called from Test cases and setConfig() which is not referenced AFAICT.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
